727424f-a.title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - 69th Street
727424f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue, south side, opposite 69th Street, show-
ing the Niederstein Hotel which was established in 1877 by Judge
Gustave Schumacher, a German immigrant. Other owners who operated
this hotel after 1892 but prior to the first mentioned owners were
Widow Catherine Schumacher, and Mrs. Catherine Sutter. Anoother
namme for this establishment was the Grand Hotel. John Niederstein Jr.
married Minnie Siebs daughter of Christopher Siebs another hotel
owner. This is a set of two views. View No.1 is viewing west;
No. 2 eastward.
1922
View 2: April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
